yload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"6761dc9e97e146b6e13c21565a8d9a614d70b4f9fbc9e3262bdf6542db5fe7a6","event_uuid":"279dafc6-6e0e-4632-a2e1-7196443a2c0d","position":{"commit_sha":"4863f94c5a3944a9529443b1d1f6a0c1b7554080","position":"1784431847356369001-279dafc6-6e0e-4632-a2e1-7196443a2c0d"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"64c2ca0da2165ae93236dd5b87b30a2ef970f50411615aed350c947ca360c27c","event_uuid":"f9887f3a-2b11-4adf-8078-b53cb1c4764c","position":{"commit_sha":"834887282a55336853ef3292bbe78132324415b3","position":"1784432176851917567-f9887f3a-2b11-4adf-8078-b53cb1c4764c"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416577550676001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## What\nThe single source of truth for every metric the command surfaces: a declarative registry mapping each metric id to its lens, data source, and compute, plus the graceful `unavailable{reason,accruing_since}` state and the `source`+`confidence` labels — so the command is written once and never modified as new signals accrue, and a classified/backfilled value is never aggregated into an authoritative structural series.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py` — new package.\n- `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` — new: `MetricSpec` (id, lens, source, confidence, compute), the `REGISTRY`, `MetricValue`/`Unavailable` result types, and an `is_authoritative(source)` segregation helper.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_registry.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nA declarative registry (not per-metric scattered code) is what makes the command complete-once: rendering iterates the registry, and a metric with no data yet returns `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` rather than being absent, so a new signal lights up by populating its source with no CLI change. `source` in {structural, git, sidecar, snapshot, backfill_classified} and `confidence` in {high, classified} ride on every value so downstream aggregation can keep high-confidence structural series apart from fuzzy backfills. Additive and standalone — no existing behavior changes.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (in-process, real registry): a metric whose compute returns no data yields `Unavailable` with populated `reason` + `accruing_since`; `is_authoritative('backfill_classified')` is False and a classified value is excluded from an authoritative rollup helper.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_registry.py` passes: every `REGISTRY` entry has a unique id, a `lens`, a `source`, and a `confidence` — asserted by collecting the registry and checking `len(ids) == len(set(ids))`.\n- [ ] A metric with no data returns `Unavailable` carrying a non-empty `reason` and an ISO `accruing_since` — unit test asserts both fields present.\n- [ ] `is_authoritative('backfill_classified')` is False and an authoritative aggregation excludes classified values — unit test asserts a mixed input yields a series containing only `source in {structural,git,sidecar,snapshot}`.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/registry.py","reason":"metric registry + label contract"},{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py","reason":"new package"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"55e66738-2e23-478d-b48c-9be3d2b0d763","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a","ticket_type":"task","title":"Metric registry + unavailable-state & source/confidence label contract","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["d170116c-8e7e-4be4-8915-8c6c99518923","0c95ee6d-c683-4e3f-b33e-54bdf904c710","d891fc16-cae3-4583-8106-1eaa8090b9a8","c1544f9d-c97d-462a-b80f-76fca15b8834","55e66738-2e23-478d-b48c-9be3d2b0d763","279dafc6-6e0e-4632-a2e1-7196443a2c0d","f9887f3a-2b11-4adf-8078-b53cb1c4764c"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784432176851917568,"uuid":"80074be5-04d5-46c1-a3ab-31a86fe2fe61"}